        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 700 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ripley, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Covington, Ripley, Halls, Nutbush, Belle Eagle, Forked Deer, Henning,
Gates, Curve, Christmasville, Orysa, Rudolph, Tibbs, Durhamville,
Gift, Oakview, Flippin, Owl City, Edward Grove, and Opossum.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
